436 *ptr++= b & 0x0f0;
437 b <<= 4;
438 *ptr++= b;
439 i--;
440 } while( i > 0 );
441 arg_int -= 8;
442 u8x8_byte_SendBytes(u8x8, 16, buf);
443 }
444
445
446 while( arg_int > 0 )
447 {
448 b = *data;
449 u8x8_byte_SendByte(u8x8, b & 0x0f0);
450 u8x8_byte_SendByte(u8x8, b << 4);
451 data++;
452 arg_int--;
453 }
454 u8x8_gpio_Delay(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_DELAY_NANO, 1);
455 break;
456 case U8X8_MSG_CAD_INIT:
457 case U8X8_MSG_CAD_START_TRANSFER:
458 case U8X8_MSG_CAD_END_TRANSFER:
459 return u8x8->byte_cb(u8x8, msg, arg_int, arg_ptr);
460 default:
461 return 0;
462 }
463 return 1;
464}

170 u8x8_cad_EndTransfer(u8x8);
171 break;
172#endif
173 case U8X8_MSG_DISPLAY_DRAW_TILE:
174 u8x8_cad_StartTransfer(u8x8);

177 x *= 8;
178 x += u8x8->x_offset;
179 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x010 | (x>>4) );
180 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x000 | ((x&15)));
181 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x0b0 | (((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->y_pos));
182
183 c = ((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->cnt;
184 c *= 8;
185 ptr = ((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->tile_ptr;
186 do
187 {
188 u8x8_cad_SendData(u8x8, c, ptr); /* note: SendData can not handle more than 255 bytes */
189 arg_int--;
190 } while( arg_int > 0 );
191
192 u8x8_cad_EndTransfer(u8x8);
193 break;
194 default:
195 return 0;
196 }

132 u8x8_cad_StartTransfer(u8x8);
133
134 x = ((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->x_pos;
135 x *= 8;
136 x += u8x8->x_offset;
137 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x020 ); /* activate chip (PD=0), horizontal increment (V=0), enter normal command set (H=0) */
138 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x080 | (x) ); /* set X address */
139 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x040 | (((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->y_pos) ); /* set Y address */
140
141 ptr = ((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->tile_ptr;
142 c = ((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->cnt;
143 c *= 8;
144 do
145 {
146 if ( c + x > 84u )
147 {
148 if ( x >= 84u )
149 break;
150 c = 84u;
151 c -= x;
152 }
153 u8x8_cad_SendData(u8x8, c, ptr); /* note: SendData can not handle more than 255 bytes */
154 x += c;
155 arg_int--;
156 } while( arg_int > 0 );
157
158 u8x8_cad_EndTransfer(u8x8);
159 break;
160 default:
161 return 0;
162 }
163 return 1;
164}

157 u8x8_cad_SendSequence(u8x8, u8x8_d_sbn1661_init_seq);
158 u8x8->cad_cb(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_CAD_END_TRANSFER, 1, NULL);
159 break;
160 case U8X8_MSG_DISPLAY_SET_POWER_SAVE:
161
162 if ( arg_int == 0 )
163 {
164 u8x8->cad_cb(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_CAD_START_TRANSFER, 0, NULL);
165 u8x8_cad_SendSequence(u8x8, u8x8_d_sbn1661_powersave0_seq);
166 u8x8->cad_cb(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_CAD_END_TRANSFER, 0, NULL);
167
168 u8x8->cad_cb(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_CAD_START_TRANSFER, 1, NULL);
169 u8x8_cad_SendSequence(u8x8, u8x8_d_sbn1661_powersave0_seq);
170 u8x8->cad_cb(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_CAD_END_TRANSFER, 1, NULL);
171 }
172 else
173 {
174 u8x8->cad_cb(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_CAD_START_TRANSFER, 0, NULL);
175 u8x8_cad_SendSequence(u8x8, u8x8_d_sbn1661_powersave1_seq);
176 u8x8->cad_cb(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_CAD_END_TRANSFER, 0, NULL);
177
178 u8x8->cad_cb(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_CAD_START_TRANSFER, 1, NULL);
179 u8x8_cad_SendSequence(u8x8, u8x8_d_sbn1661_powersave1_seq);
180 u8x8->cad_cb(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_CAD_END_TRANSFER, 1, NULL);
181
182 }
183 break;
184 case U8X8_MSG_DISPLAY_DRAW_TILE:
185
186 ptr = ((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->tile_ptr;
187 // x and c are ignored (u8g2 only)
188 //x = ((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->x_pos;
189 //c = ((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->cnt;
190
191 u8x8->cad_cb(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_CAD_START_TRANSFER, 0, NULL);
192 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x000 | 0); // column 0
193 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x0b8 | (((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->y_pos));
194 u8x8_cad_SendData(u8x8, 61, ptr); /* note: SendData can not handle more than 255 bytes */
195 u8x8->cad_cb(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_CAD_END_TRANSFER, 0, NULL);
196
197 ptr += 61;
198
199 u8x8->cad_cb(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_CAD_START_TRANSFER, 1, NULL);
200 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x000 | 0); // column 0
201 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x0b8 | (((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->y_pos));
202
203 u8x8_cad_SendData(u8x8, 61, ptr); /* note: SendData can not handle more than 255 bytes */
204 u8x8->cad_cb(u8x8, U8X8_MSG_CAD_END_TRANSFER, 1, NULL);
205
206 break;
207 default:
208 return 0;
209 }
210 return 1;

346 x += u8x8->x_offset;
347 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x010 | (x>>4) );
348 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x000 | ((x&15)));
349 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x0b0 | (((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->y_pos));
350
351 c = ((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->cnt;
352 c *= 8;
353 ptr = ((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->tile_ptr;
354 /*
355 The following if condition checks the hardware limits of the st7567
356 controller: It is not allowed to write beyond the display limits.
357 This is in fact an issue within flip mode.
358 */
359 if ( c + x > 132u )
360 {
361 c = 132u;
362 c -= x;
363 }
364 do
365 {
366 u8x8_cad_SendData(u8x8, c, ptr); /* note: SendData can not handle more than 255 bytes */
367 arg_int--;
368 } while( arg_int > 0 );
369
370 u8x8_cad_EndTransfer(u8x8);
371 break;
372 default:
373 return 0;
374 }
375 return 1;

Definition at line 171 of file u8x8_d_st7586s_erc240160.c.

171 {
172
173 uint8_t c;
174 uint8_t *ptr;
175 uint8_t i, byte;
176 uint32_t input;
177 uint8_t output[4];
178 switch (msg) {
179 case U8X8_MSG_DISPLAY_DRAW_TILE:
180 u8x8_cad_StartTransfer(u8x8); // OK Start transfer
181 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x02B); /* Row Address Setting */
182 u8x8_cad_SendArg(u8x8, 0x000);
183 u8x8_cad_SendArg(u8x8, 0x008 * ((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->y_pos);
184 u8x8_cad_SendArg(u8x8, 0x000);
185 u8x8_cad_SendArg(u8x8, 0x09F); // should set end row based on display dimensions
186 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x02C); /* cmd write display data to ram */
187 c = ((u8x8_tile_t *) arg_ptr)->cnt; //
188 c *= 8;
189 ptr = ((u8x8_tile_t *) arg_ptr)->tile_ptr; //
190
191// The ST7586S has an unusual 3 pixels per byte format the ERC240160 is even more annoying
192// as it has every 3rd COM line disconnected for extra oddness so here we read in a byte
193// (8 pixels) and pack that into 4 bytes of 2 pixels + 1 unused each. This has to be done
194// in a different order for flipped, normal UUx11x22 flipped 11x22xUU
195 while (c > 0) {
196 input = ((uint8_t)ptr[0]);
197
198 for (i=0; i<4; i++)
199 {
200 byte = 0;
201 if (u8x8->x_offset ==0){
202 if (input & 0x80) // if bit 7
203 byte = byte | 0x18; //set pixel 1
204 if (input & 0x40) // if bit 6
205 byte = byte | 0x3; //set pixel 2
206 }
207 if (u8x8->x_offset ==1){
208 if (input & 0x80) // if bit 7
209 byte = byte | 0xC0; //set pixel 1
210 if (input & 0x40) // if bit 6
211 byte = byte | 0x18; //set pixel 2
212 }
213 output[i] = byte;
214 input <<= 2;
215 }
216
217 u8x8_cad_SendData(u8x8, 4, output);
218 ptr += 1;
219 c -= 1;
220 }
221 u8x8_cad_EndTransfer(u8x8);
222 break;
223 case U8X8_MSG_DISPLAY_INIT:
224 u8x8_d_helper_display_init(u8x8);
225 u8x8_cad_SendSequence(u8x8, u8x8_d_st7586s_erc240160_init_seq);
226 break;
227 case U8X8_MSG_DISPLAY_SETUP_MEMORY:
228 u8x8_d_helper_display_setup_memory(u8x8, &u8x8_st7586s_erc240160_display_info);
229 break;
230 case U8X8_MSG_DISPLAY_SET_FLIP_MODE:
231 if ( arg_int == 0 )
232 {
233 u8x8_cad_SendSequence(u8x8, u8x8_d_st7586s_erc240160_flip0_seq);
234 u8x8->x_offset = u8x8->display_info->default_x_offset;
235 }
236 else
237 {
238 u8x8_cad_SendSequence(u8x8, u8x8_d_st7586s_erc240160_flip1_seq);
239 u8x8->x_offset = u8x8->display_info->flipmode_x_offset;
240 }
241 break;
242 case U8X8_MSG_DISPLAY_SET_POWER_SAVE:
243 if (arg_int == 0)
244 u8x8_cad_SendSequence(u8x8, u8x8_d_st7586s_sleep_off);
245 else
246 u8x8_cad_SendSequence(u8x8, u8x8_d_st7586s_sleep_on);
247 break;
248#ifdef U8X8_WITH_SET_CONTRAST
249 case U8X8_MSG_DISPLAY_SET_CONTRAST:
250 u8x8_cad_StartTransfer(u8x8);
251 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x0C0);
252 u8x8_cad_SendArg(u8x8, arg_int);
253 u8x8_cad_SendArg(u8x8, 1);
254 u8x8_cad_EndTransfer(u8x8);
255 break;
256#endif
257 default:
258 return 0;
259 }
260 return 1;
261}

195 byte = byte | 0x18; //set pixel 2

197 byte = byte | 0x3; //set pixel 3
198 output[i] = byte;
199 input <<= 3;
200 }

202 ptr += 3;
203 c -= 3;
204 }
205 u8x8_cad_EndTransfer(u8x8);

208 u8x8_d_helper_display_init(u8x8);

273 u8x8_cad_SendArg(u8x8, arg_int ); /* uc1601 has range from 0 to 255 */
274 u8x8_cad_EndTransfer(u8x8);
275 break;
276#endif

278 u8x8_cad_StartTransfer(u8x8);

281 x *= 8;

284 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x000 | ((x&15)));
285 u8x8_cad_SendCmd(u8x8, 0x0b0 | (((u8x8_tile_t *)arg_ptr)->y_pos));

293 arg_int--;
294 } while( arg_int > 0 );
295
296 u8x8_cad_EndTransfer(u8x8);
297 break;
298 default:
299 return 0;
300 }

196 }
197 break;
198 default:
199 u8x8->debounce_state--; /* count down, until there is a valid state */

Definition at line 304 of file u8x8_8x8.c.

305{
306 if ( b == 0 || b == '\n' ) /* '\n' terminates the string to support the string list procedures */
307 return 0x0ffff; /* end of string detected, pending UTF8 is discarded */
308 if ( u8x8->utf8_state == 0 )
309 {
310 if ( b >= 0xfc ) /* 6 byte sequence */
311 {
312 u8x8->utf8_state = 5;
313 b &= 1;
314 }
315 else if ( b >= 0xf8 )
316 {
317 u8x8->utf8_state = 4;
318 b &= 3;
319 }
320 else if ( b >= 0xf0 )
321 {
322 u8x8->utf8_state = 3;
323 b &= 7;
324 }
325 else if ( b >= 0xe0 )
326 {
327 u8x8->utf8_state = 2;
328 b &= 15;
329 }
330 else if ( b >= 0xc0 )

333 b &= 0x01f;
334 }
335 else

338 return b;
339 }
